just_use split_for_set.go

# label: INTRICATE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Hand card V finds two same-value, different-suit extractable board cards;
the three cards together form a new 3-set.

**Index stability.** Apply relocates each target by card identity
(relocate, shared with peel_for_run) on the current board, since earlier
plays this turn may have shifted indices. Defined in this file as the
canonical home for the helper.

pickTwoDistinctSuits also rejects candidates matching the hand card's
suit — you need THREE distinct suits in the final set.
